      { name: "Epinephrine (low-dose)", type: "Catecholamine Inotrope/Vasopressor", action: "At low doses (0.01-0.1 mcg/kg/min), predominantly beta-1 effect increasing contractility and heart rate", sideEffects: "Tachycardia, arrhythmias, hyperglycemia, lactic acidosis at high doses", contra: "None absolute in LCOS", pearl: "Low-dose epinephrine (0.03-0.05 mcg/kg/min) provides inotropy without excessive vasoconstriction. Often combined with milrinone for synergistic inotropic and afterload-reducing effects." }
