    pearls: ["LCOS is PREDICTABLE: peak onset 6-18 hours post-CPB. Proactive milrinone initiation prevents hemodynamic deterioration.", "SvO2 is the single best real-time indicator of cardiac output adequacy: <60% = inadequate delivery, <40% = critical", "Rising lactate is the earliest biochemical sign of LCOS: trend every 2-4 hours and respond to upward trends", "NIRS provides continuous, non-invasive monitoring of regional oxygen delivery: falling trends precede clinical deterioration", "In neonates, heart rate is the primary determinant of cardiac output: temporary pacing optimizes CO when intrinsic rate is suboptimal", "Milrinone has a long half-life (2-3 hours in children): plan ahead and do not expect rapid hemodynamic changes with dose adjustments"],
