      { question: "A child post-cardiac surgery has a lactate of 6.5 mmol/L, SvO2 of 42%, and is on maximal milrinone and epinephrine. Next step?", options: ["Add dopamine", "Increase IV fluids to 20 mL/kg bolus", "Emergent ECMO cannulation for refractory LCOS", "Observe for 2 more hours"], correct: 2, rationale: "Refractory LCOS unresponsive to maximal medical therapy (optimized preload, afterload reduction, inotropic support) requires mechanical circulatory support with ECMO to prevent irreversible organ injury." }
